Human rights lawyer George Bizos will be laid to rest on Thursday. He died at his home last week at the age of 92. JOHANNESBURG - Human rights lawyer George Bizos will be laid to rest on Thursday at Westpark Cemetery. He's been accorded Special Official Funeral. READ: Flags will fly at half-mast to honour George Bizos The funeral is taking place at a Greek Orthodox Church in Johannesburg. Bizos died at his home last week at the age of 92. Many have praised Bizos for his dedication in the fight for human rights, with President Cyril Ramaphosa hailing him as one of the architects of our Constitution.